{"display":"Modify this repository in the following ways. 1. Add a Google Gemini integration such that, if the user has an active Google account, then a button will be on the right side to provide feedback for their input. 2. The example text in each form field should be gray, and disappear when the user adds their own input. It should reappear in gray if the user removes all of their input from each form field.","pastedContents":{},"timestamp":1773176663570,"project":"/home/rstahl/src/repos/rhr-project-intake","sessionId":"7e205cfa-d4f7-45b6-9557-892d401da53f"}
{"display":"Create a build script, in bash, that does the following. 1. Verify that all of the required prerequisites are installed. If not, exit and list the missing prerequities. 2. Run appropriate linters and syntax validation against all code in the \"webpage\" directory. If there are errors, write them in a file named \"AGENT_TODO\" in the repository base directory. If there are errors, exit and direct the user to correct those errors listed in AGENT_TODO. 3. Execute a Docker build. You will need to create the Dockerfile. 4. Create a bash script named \"entrypoint.bash\" that will work both from a user's machine and from within the container that is built by the Dockerfile.","pastedContents":{},"timestamp":1773177436313,"project":"/home/rstahl/src/repos/rhr-project-intake","sessionId":"7e205cfa-d4f7-45b6-9557-892d401da53f"}
